[
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't read Japanese and so don't know which parts of how the kana is rendered are important and which are stylistic (e.g. for the letter \"q\" it's important that the line extend down visibly below the circle to distinguish from \"a\", but it's optional if the line extends a tiny bit above the tangent). Anyone here have any tips?</p>",
        "id": 219204733,
        "sender_full_name": "Shea Levy",
        "timestamp": 1607433329
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>e.g. the first stroke in the stroke order on wikipedia curves/angles up a bit, does that matter?</p>",
        "id": 219204757,
        "sender_full_name": "Shea Levy",
        "timestamp": 1607433353
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Usually it does not, but as you say the stroke order is important when you write Kana and Kanji.</p>",
        "id": 219204881,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1607433434
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>よ (Yo) is a rather recognizable kana anyway. What you say becomes more important for other kana, especially the katakana シ (shi) - ツ (tsu) and ン (n) - ソ (so), where as you can see the orientation of the stroke matters a great deal. <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 219205190,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1607433638
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anyway I've been studying Japanese for a bit but I'm by no means a native speaker, so someone will most likely have better insights than I do about this</p>",
        "id": 219205262,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1607433697
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My impression is that as long as you've got a general upside-down F shape with a clear loop at the lower left corner, it will likely be recognizable as よ.<br>\nIn my own English-language-biased shortcut, I think of よ as similar to a cursive L.  (I also think of the Greek letter <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span></span></span></span> as similar to a cursive E, after I got tired of writing <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span></span></span></span> as a messy squiggle in my undergrad physics classes.)</p>",
        "id": 219239520,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607450206
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess you see it differently when the currency you grew up with is £</p>",
        "id": 219246291,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1607453450
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Probably so.  I considered using £ as a comparison, but in the typeface I see here on Zulip, there are two problems – the horizontal stroke goes all the way through, and there is no loop.</p>",
        "id": 219246527,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607453584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For me the one similar to E has always been epsilon. And yes, I've also alwyas perceived xi as uselessly complicated xD</p>",
        "id": 219248713,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1607454652
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just realized the other day that small xi <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span></span></span></span> is supposed to look like a sorta cursive big xi <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 219248894,
        "sender_full_name": "Joe Moeller",
        "timestamp": 1607454731
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I always thought it was just sorta random.</p>",
        "id": 219248924,
        "sender_full_name": "Joe Moeller",
        "timestamp": 1607454746
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Greek doesn't have cursive fwiw</p>",
        "id": 219248936,
        "sender_full_name": "Giorgos Bakirtzis",
        "timestamp": 1607454757
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's why I said \"sorta\" <span aria-label=\"wink\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f609\" role=\"img\" title=\"wink\">:wink:</span></p>",
        "id": 219248988,
        "sender_full_name": "Joe Moeller",
        "timestamp": 1607454791
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275914\">Joe Moeller</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229451-general.3A-off-topic/topic/Writing.20.E3.82.88.3F/near/219248894\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I just realized the other day that small xi <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span></span></span></span> is supposed to look like a sorta cursive big xi <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Big Xi is a dope letter tho</p>",
        "id": 219249808,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1607455263
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And not to be confused with 三, since we're talking about writing Japanese characters.  <span aria-label=\"stuck out tongue wink\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f61c\" role=\"img\" title=\"stuck out tongue wink\">:stuck_out_tongue_wink:</span></p>",
        "id": 219249983,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607455369
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The way we write Ξ actually looks more like that 三</p>",
        "id": 219250996,
        "sender_full_name": "Giorgos Bakirtzis",
        "timestamp": 1607455877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ξ Ξ are the normal ways of writing it</p>",
        "id": 219251172,
        "sender_full_name": "Giorgos Bakirtzis",
        "timestamp": 1607455958
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As I see it, the defining difference between <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span> and 三 is in the relative lengths of the top and bottom lines.  With careful orthography, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span> has both with the same length.  Similarly careful orthography will have 三 where the top line is slightly shorter than the bottom line.</p>",
        "id": 219251735,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607456234
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah greek Ξ is symmetric although it can be written the japanese way too (and people often do)</p>",
        "id": 219251831,
        "sender_full_name": "Giorgos Bakirtzis",
        "timestamp": 1607456276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hence the emphasis on <em>careful orthography</em>.  (:</p>",
        "id": 219251938,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607456310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"309257\">Jason Erbele</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229451-general.3A-off-topic/topic/Writing.20.E3.82.88.3F/near/219251735\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>As I see it, the defining difference between <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span> and 三 is in the relative lengths of the top and bottom lines.  With careful orthography, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span> has both with the same length.  Similarly careful orthography will have 三 where the top line is slightly shorter than the bottom line.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It's also worth pointing out that by \"careful ortography\" you are basically meaning \"some computer fonts\". Calligraphy is a big thing in many countries, Japan included. I think we could discuss for ages about what really defines the \"essence\" of a symbol/character/kanji. <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 219254294,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1607457555
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Fair point about calligraphy – I have limited exposure to Japanese calligraphy.  However, I wouldn't go so far as to conflate my \"careful orthography\" with \"some computer fonts\".  Maybe it's not true for everyone, but I know my own handwriting differs when I am hastily writing versus when I focus on neat penmanship.  It is certainly an aesthetic issue, and computerized typefaces likely have a reasonably strong influence.</p>",
        "id": 219263742,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607462200
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>More generally speaking, a \"poorly formed\" character (whether scribbled or written by someone unfamiliar with the character) and a \"fanciful calligraphic\" character can both depart radically from \"standard\" computerized typefaces, and even subvert expected norms for a character, while still being recognizable.  But I would wager that a sizable majority of calligraphic 三s carefully make all three strokes differ in length.</p>",
        "id": 219263766,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607462213
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you are trying to communicate with a handwritten よ in isolation from the rest of the Japanese language, which is what seems to have spurred this digression, my opinion is that an \"ugly\" よ is fine.  You can look up the accepted stroke order and direction for hiragana for guidance, but if you can create a recognizable よ more quickly with a different stroke order/direction, I won't tattle.  But practice with the \"proper\" way to write it will likely make your よs \"prettier\" over time.</p>",
        "id": 219263928,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1607462286
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's probably worth mentioning that this is the correct stroke order for よ - you write the cross bar first, and then the rest of it, which is different from £</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/8VYxAEUfaq5Mj0Q5bGyX95ft/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/8VYxAEUfaq5Mj0Q5bGyX95ft/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/8VYxAEUfaq5Mj0Q5bGyX95ft/image.png\"></a></div><p>If you write it this way you should naturally end up with a nice vertical line on the second stroke</p>",
        "id": 219285955,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1607475769
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>≡</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\equiv</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.46375em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≡</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p><span aria-label=\"upside down\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f643\" role=\"img\" title=\"upside down\">:upside_down:</span></p>",
        "id": 219288838,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1607478355
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's a funny story about Barry Mazur trying to wind up Serge Lang by using the expression <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mfrac><mover accent=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi><mo>ˉ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\frac{\\bar\\Xi}{\\Xi}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.3130769999999998em;vertical-align:-0.345em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9680769999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.6550000000000002em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">Ξ</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.394em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord accent mtight\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8201099999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mtight\">Ξ</span></span><span style=\"top:-2.9523300000000003em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.25em;\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">ˉ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.345em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span> in a talk. (p547 <a href=\"http://www.ams.org/notices/200605/fea-lang.pdf\">http://www.ams.org/notices/200605/fea-lang.pdf</a>)</p>",
        "id": 219309845,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1607503830
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>While on sabbatical at Harvard, he sat in on a course Mazur was giving and often criticized the notation. Eventually they decided to give him a T-shirt which said, “This notation sucks” on it. So one day Barry intentionally tried to get him to say it. He introduced a complex variable <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span>, took its complex conjugate, and divided by the original <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span></span>. This was written as a vertical fraction, so it looked like eight horizontal lines on the blackboard. He then did a few other similar things, but Serge kept quiet—apparently he didn’t criticize notation unless he knew what the underlying mathematics was about. Eventually Barry had to give up and just present him with the T-shirt.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 219309909,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1607503895
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So if you want to introduce a notation for a real number and Serge Lang was in the audience, you'd just write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi><mo>≡</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\Xi \\equiv \\overline{\\Xi}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≡</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8833300000000001em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord overline\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8833300000000001em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">Ξ</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.80333em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"overline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, or if it's nonzero just</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mfrac><mover accent=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ξ</mi></mfrac><mo>≡</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\frac{\\overline{\\Xi}}{\\Xi} \\equiv 1 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.388831em;vertical-align:-0.345em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.043831em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.6550000000000002em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">Ξ</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.394em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord overline mtight\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9283300000000001em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">Ξ</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.83033em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"overline-line mtight\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.049em;\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.345em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≡</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 219389983,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1607544075
    }
]